        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>U. S. Circuit Clerks Office</placeName>
            </p>
            <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>St Paul</placeName>, <date>Nov. 20. 1862</date></p>
            <p><addressee>Revd Isaac Leeser</addressee>.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">My dear Sir.</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">The package containing<lb/> the books and letters arrived here on the<lb/>
                <date>18<hi rend="sup">th</hi></date> inst, and therein enclose the amount<lb/> of
                your bill &amp; 5.53. which I trust will<lb/> come safe to hand.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I have delayed till to day to forward<lb/> this in hopes to be able
                to send you a<lb/> list of subscribers for the Occident, and<lb/> also to order some
                copies of the Bible<lb/> but I have not had time to give the<lb/> matter much
                attention. I have sold<lb/> 1 copy of the Bible, and have no doubt<lb/> if I had
                them here could dispose<lb/> of Â½ a dozen at least, and obtain<lb/> the cash on
                delivery and would remit<lb/> it at once. I also trust in my next<lb/> communication
                which I will write</p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>in about a week from this to send<lb/> you a list of half dozen subscribers<lb/> for
                the Occident in their city! All tho<lb/> Israelites here are Germans and can<lb/>
                read but little English and therefore<lb/> I do not suppose that much could be<lb/>
                done in the sale of <persName>Dias'</persName> letters, tho' I<lb/> shall endeavor
                to dispose of the two<lb/> copies sent and if more are required<lb/> will inform
                you.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I understand that you have a<lb/> much smaller and cheaper
                edition<lb/> of the bibleâif so, I could dispose<lb/> of some for you; at this
                season of<lb/> the year the expense of sending a<lb/> package here is more than it
                would<lb/> be in the summer time when the<lb/> river is open for navigation. Do
                you<lb/> count the expense of transmitting<lb/> the books <add>?</add>? I will
                willingly<lb/> do all I can to dispose of any of<lb/> your publications, and you
                can<lb/> send them if you think best at</p>
            <pb n="3"/>
            <p>any time; and may depend upon<lb/> speedy remittance as they are sold.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">My time is fully occupied here<lb/> as I have the whole charge of
                the<lb/> U. S <sic>Marshal's</sic> office together with the<lb/> Deputy clerkship in
                the District and<lb/> Circuit Court but as the place is small<lb/> and I am
                acquainted with every body<lb/> it will not inconvenience me in any<lb/> way to give
                attention to any matter you<lb/> may entrust to my care; In my next<lb/> I will
                forward names of Officers of the<lb/> Congregation.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">My family are very well, and<lb/> enjoy the climate here very much.
                My<lb/> oldest child <persName>Nellie</persName> is a pupil of <persName>Mr.<lb/>
                    Marcuson</persName> in the Hebrew and religion<lb/> and the three occupy
                        <persName><sic>Rachels</sic></persName> time<lb/> continually. She desires
                to be remembered<lb/> to you. <persName>Mr. Cohen</persName> has left <placeName>St
                    Paul</placeName><lb/> and resides in <placeName>Chicago</placeName>.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Very Respy Yours</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">
                <persName role="author">J. N. Cardoza</persName>
            </p>
        </body>
